-- Hungarian RFV's First Bond Offering Oversubscribed by 67%, Plans New Sale
-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 2010-09-30T07:52:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-30/hungarian-rfv-s-first-bond-offering-oversubscribed-by-67-plans-new-sale.html
RFV Nyrt. , a Hungarian energy
equipment group, said a corporate bond sale was oversubscribed
by 67 percent, prompting the company to close the offering
earlier than expected.  RFV, which offered 2 billion forint ($9.8 million) of
company debt, received bids worth 3.35 billion forint and plans
a new sale in November, the company said in a statement posted
on the  website  of the Budapest Stock Exchange.  Shareholders authorized the management to sell 10 billion
forint of corporate bonds over the next 12 months, the company
said on Sept. 17.  The bonds, which have a maturity of 3.5 years, carry an
annual fixed coupon of 10.44 percent.  Proceeds of the debt sale will be used to finance projects
in Romania, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
